# Data Layer & Sanity Migration Path

## Data Storage

Store all content in `lib/data/` organized by type:

```
lib/data/
├── site-config.ts
├── navigation.ts
├── pages/
│   ├── home.ts
│   └── about.ts
└── content/
    ├── services.ts
    └── team.ts
```

## TypeScript Interfaces

Define interfaces in `lib/types/` for every data structure. Every page data object must include:

```typescript
seo: {
  metaTitle: string;
  metaDescription: string;
  slug: string;
  keywords?: string[];
  ogImageUrl?: string;
}
```

Structure data objects to mirror future Sanity CMS schemas (nested objects, arrays, references).

## Component Rules

- Components are **pure presentational**: accept props → return JSX → no data fetching
- Never import data directly in components — always receive via props
- Never hardcode text/content in JSX

## Page Rules

- Pages import data from `lib/data/` and pass to components via props
- Every page must export `generateMetadata()` using the page's SEO data

## Sanity Migration

Code is structured so migrating to Sanity only requires:

1. Change page imports: `import { data } from '@/lib/data/page'` → `const data = await sanityFetch()`
2. Components remain unchanged (already accept props)
3. Types already match future Sanity schema structure
